args:
During a break from their training, Celliera
recounts a terrifying legend about the volcano.
But just as she does so, it eruptsâ€”and a cry
for help reaches the prince's ears.
LEFT, RIGHT! LEFT, RIGHT! LEFT, RIGHT!\n...I CAN'T HEEEEEAR YOU!
IS THAT YOUR VOICE, OR DID A CRICKET\nFART OVER THERE?!
ELISANNE! RANZAL! Swing those arms!\nLift those thighs! I WANNA SEE ACTION!
What's the holdup, Cleo?! When I say to\nshow me grit, YOU GIVE ME A DESERT!
Any fiend gets in your way, YOU GIVE\nTHEM THE BOOT! Got it, whelps?!
She's the biggest fiend of all...
AAAND...break! All right, pups, take five. \nCleo, remember to breathe over there.
I fancied myself in fairly good shape,\nbut my legs are quaking like butter.
I knew you lot were something special.\nMost of my students break down in tears\nten minutes into the ol' fiend marathon.
But you're right. Now that it's over,\nI DO feel stronger than before.
Who said it was over? NO ONE SAID THAT!\nWe're just getting STARTED!
Once break time's up, I'll have you do\nburpees all the way up to the summit!

My teaching style is shock and awe.
I'm not here to ask your muscles politelyâ€”
I'm here to dominate your flabby abs!
And I DO NOT TAKE PRISONERS.
Do we at least get something to drink?\nI'm dyin' here!
...Take this. It's water steeped with\nvarious healing herbs.
Th-thank you... Goodness, this is delicious.
Running up a mountain is bad enough,\nbut a volcano? I'm melting in this heat!
In that case, I've got just the story to put a\nchill up your spine...
Stay hydrated, everyone, because this will\nhave you wetting your smallclothes.\nNow...SIT UP AND LISTEN!
A thousand years ago, a kingdom called\nAlba stood on this very spot.
And on its throne sat Archeoleâ€”a king\nprotected by a mighty dragon.
A king with a dragon?\nSounds like {player_name}.
Archeole was great and wise,\nbrave and just.
So fine a king was he that the dragon took\nhim for its master of its own free will.
Alba rose to heights of prosperity unknown\nin any age before. Until one day, when it\nmerely...vanished.
I know kingdoms fall, but I've never heard\nof one that simply vanished.
People? Gone. Houses? Gone.\nKing? Dragon? Throne? Castle?\n...All gone.
They were never seen again...but to this\nday, their voices are said to haunt this\nvery mountain.
Their wails cry out to the living...\nBECKONING THEM TO THEIR DOOOOOOM!
(If my ears weren't playing tricks, then\nmaybe I actually heard a ghost of Alba!)
(No, that can't be right. It seemed to\nbear the living no ill will...)
Heh heh heh... Scared, are we?
Bored. No offense, but yer a way better\ntrainer than a storyteller.
What?! That's not possible! Admit itâ€”\nyou're terrified!
When I told that tale to my students,\nthey were petrified. One even passed out!
...Er, wait. Was that why they ran like mad\nwhen that fiend appeared?
Augh! Then that was my own dumb fault.\nI can't well blame them for getting scared\nwhen I'm the one scaring them.
AHEM! ...Er, nothing. Just thinking up a\nnew way to make you whelps puke.
Now then, you've rested long enough.\nBACK TO TRAINâ€”
It's enormous... I've never seen such a\ncreature before!
That's him! The one I told you about!
Was that some sort of mirage?
Oh, GROSS! Whatever it puked up,\nit STINKS!
*sniff* That's sulfur... But wait, does that\nmean the volcano is becoming active?
Regardless, at this rate it could erupt at\nany moment!
Our hunt isn't over, but I can't risk their\nlives for this...
Everyone, back down the mountain! Hurry!
I hear it loud and clear this time!
As do I. They seem to be begging for help.
It's coming from the back of the cavern.\nLet's go!
He don't care how dangerous it is, lady.\nIf someone needs help, he's there.
And we're dumb enough to follow him.\nAnyway, why don't ya head down the\nmountain ahead of us, yeah?
...No. I am your armsmaster,\nand you are my students!
If you're risking your lives for a rescue,\nI'll not run and save myself alone!
